	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A linear voltage regulator. The 7805 regulates its output to 5V, provided it has suffisent voltage at its input. It should be near the place where you plug the AC adapter in the NES.
<br />
<br />(If you're curious, check this <a href="http://www.google.ca/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=7805&amp;source=web&amp;cd=2&amp;ved=0CDQQFjAB&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.national.com%2Fds%2FLM%2FLM340.pdf&amp;ei=23mjToXKEebi0QHmovS0Bg&amp;usg=AFQjCNFwINVOAjxCe_UED7KKxCPhixj9Ag&amp;sig2=1_bKDGzL9z4BRrfUd3kI5Q" class="postlink">datasheet</a>)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


