	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I guess they now make switching power supplies which does not dissipate heat that can replace 77xx regulators in most applications.
<br />
<br />The way the power suply of the NES has been engineered is plain stupid, if the NES uses 1W of power, it will dissipate ~2W in heat. A switching regulator is the only way to solve this problem.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


